==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cottage
<hw>Cot"tage</hw> <pr>(k?t"t?j; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Cot</er> a cottage.]</ety> <def>A small house; a cot; a
hut.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term was formerly limited to a habitation for the
poor, but is now applied to any small tasteful dwelling; and at places
of summer resort, to any residence or lodging house of rustic
architecture, irrespective of size.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cottage allotment</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Alloment</er>.</cd> <mark>[Eng.]</mark> -- <col><b>Cottage
cheese</b></col>, <cd>the thick part of clabbered milk strained, salted,
and pressed into a ball.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cottaged</ent>⟦br⟧
